SIMPLE: throughout
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Throughout
<hw>Through*out"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prep.</pos> <def>Quite through;
from one extremity to the other of; also, every part of; <as>as, to
search <ex>throughout</ex> the house</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor to their idle orbs doth sight appear⟦br⟧
Of sun, or moon, or star, <qex>throughout</qex> the year.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throughout</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Throughout
<hw>Through*out"</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In every part; <as>as, the
cloth was of a piece <ex>throughout</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Throve</ent>⟦br⟧
